DSA Interview Notes – LeetCode 347: Top K Frequent Elements
Problem Statement

Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return the k most frequent elements.

The answer can be returned in any order.

Example
Input:

nums = [1,1,1,2,2,3]

k = 2

Output:

[1,2]
Step 1: Understanding the Problem

We need to return the elements that appear the maximum number of times.

The problem can be divided into two parts:

Count the frequency of every element.
Retrieve the top k elements having the highest frequency.
Brute Force Approach
Idea
Count the frequency using a HashMap.
Sort all the entries according to their frequencies.
Return the first k elements.
Time Complexity
O(n log n)

Sorting dominates the complexity.

Observation

Do we really need to sort all the frequencies?

Suppose

nums = [1,1,1,2,2,3]

k = 1

After building the frequency map

1 → 3

2 → 2

3 → 1

Sorting all three entries is unnecessary because we only need one answer.

Can we avoid sorting?

Yes.

Key Observation

The maximum frequency of any element can never exceed the size of the array.

If

nums.length = n

then

Maximum Frequency = n

Therefore,

the possible frequencies are

